<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-284-118  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 284 118.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computerworld  March 26 1990 v24 n13 p80(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Software for political advantage. (Elfin, an energy-useforecasting program)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Wilder, Clinton.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Elfin is an energy-use forecasting program developed by DanKirshner, an economic analyst for the Environmental Defense Fund(EDF).andP;  The software has become the standard for Californiautilities applying for rate adjustments or new construction.andO;Developed in the late 1970s as a component of EDF's campaignagainst nuclear and coal plant construction, Elfin has sinceinfluenced energy planning in California and is now used as abusiness planning tool by the same utilities that EDF used tofight.andP;  The program is available in micro and mainframe versions.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Product:   Elfin (Computer program) (business use).andO;Topic:     Software packagesEnvironmental protectionUser-Written SoftwareEnergy ManagementEnvironmental Defense Fund.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andO;Person:    Kirshner, Dan (innovations).andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>